      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "> Why constrain this to apple?\r\n\r\nNot to apple, but I guess one reason to scope this (to aarch64) would be to avoid `Wunused-command-line-argument` warnings on x86_64. Which now appear in the CI (https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/actions/runs/6381638188/job/17318511090?pr=28459#step:7:1979):\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n   CXX      libbitcoin_node_a-deploymentstatus.o\r\nclang: error: argument unused during compilation: '-mbranch-protection=bti' [-Werror,-Wunused-command-line-argument]\r\n```",
      "commit_id" : "8f48576f1130daaa3746858db6e845c40a90d551",
      "created_at" : "2023-10-02T15:09:18Z",
      "diff_hunk" : "@@ -965,6 +965,11 @@ if test \"$use_hardening\" != \"no\"; then\n       ;;\n   esac\n \n+  case $host in\n+    *aarch64-apple*)\n+      AX_CHECK_COMPILE_FLAG([-mbranch-protection=bti], [HARDENED_CXXFLAGS=\"$HARDENED_CXXFLAGS -mbranch-protection=bti\"])",
